{
  "stem": "12255.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We have 40 or 50 young Jews whose only crime is they were trying to get across the border to get into Europe and to eventually join into illegal immigration to go to the land of Israel.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He said, we have to stop them, but I don't think this was the place in which to bring them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is a Nazi criminal camp for Nazi criminals and not for them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he took me into the camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He took me to them, and I got them together.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were, of course, overjoyed to see a Jew, or a Jewish officer.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we davened, we prayed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had the afternoon and evening service.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I promised them that within a few days, they would be out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The next-- I went back to my camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the next morning I went up to the headquarters, and I asked to see the brigadier.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, as a chaplain, I suppose he thought I'd come to discuss some religious matter with him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I got admission.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I told him in no uncertain terms that this was the wrong thing and that I was reporting to headquarter-- to my headquarters in London.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And if something was not done, it would be publicized all over the world.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I said, I want these people out of that camp immediately.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We can take them to Bergen-Belsen, but not in that camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he immediately-- I must say, he immediately gave the order.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I went then to the Jewish relief organization, which had-- their vans all had big Magen Davids on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were the equivalent of Red Cross kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the next day, we rode through all these Nazi, Nazis, and loaded up these people, and took them to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
